<doc id="41293" wikidata="Q6085479" url="?curid=41293" title="Isochronous signal">
<text>In telecommunications, an isochronous signal is a signal in which the time interval separating any two significant instants is equal to the unit interval or a multiple of the unit interval. Variations in the time intervals are constrained within specified limits.

&quot;Isochronous&quot; is a characteristic of one signal, while &quot;synchronous&quot; indicates a relationship between two or more signals.

