<doc id="41311" wikidata="Q6505539" url="?curid=41311" title="Layered system">
<text>In telecommunications, a layered system is a system in which components are grouped, &quot;i.e.&quot;, layered, in a hierarchical arrangement, such that lower layers provide functions and services that support the functions and services of higher layers. 

Systems of ever-increasing complexity and capability can be built by adding or changing the layers to improve overall system capability while using the components that are still in place.</text><links>
