<doc id="41392" wikidata="Q6966329" url="?curid=41392" title="Narrowband modem">
<text>In telecommunications, a narrowband modem is a modem whose modulated output signal has an essential frequency spectrum that is limited to that which can be wholly contained within, and faithfully transmitted through, a voice channel with a nominal 4 kHz bandwidth. 

&quot;Note:&quot; High frequency (HF) modems are limited to operation over a voice channel with a nominal 3 kHz bandwidth.

