<doc id="41414" wikidata="Q16908574" url="?curid=41414" title="Neutral direct-current telegraph system">
<text>In telecommunications, a neutral direct-current telegraph system (&quot;single-current system&quot;, &quot;single-current transmission system&quot;, &quot;single-Morse system&quot;) is a telegraph system in which (a) current flows during marking intervals and no current flows during spacing intervals for the transmission of signals over a line, and (b) the direction of current flow (electric polarity) is immaterial.

==See also==
