<doc id="41448" wikidata="Q7096395" url="?curid=41448" title="Open network architecture">
<text>In telecommunications, and in the context of Federal Communications Commission&#x27;s (FCC) Computer Inquiry III, Open network architecture (ONA) is the overall design of a communication carrier&#x27;s basic network facilities and services to permit all users of the basic network to interconnect to specific basic network functions and interfaces on an unbundled, equal-access basis.

The ONA concept consists of three integral components:

# Basic serving arrangements (BSAs)
# Basic service elements (BSEs)
# Complementary network services

