<doc id="41496" wikidata="Q7254460" url="?curid=41496" title="Pseudo bit error ratio">
<text>Pseudo bit error ratio (PBER) in adaptive high-frequency (HF) radio, is a bit error ratio derived by majority logic decoding to processes redundant transmissions. 

&quot;Note:&quot; In adaptive HF radio automatic link establishment, PBER is determined by the extent of error correction, such as by using the fraction of non-unanimous votes in the 2-of-3 majority decoder. </text><links>
